Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt: No Contact Order signed and filed.
Court ordered Justice Point Pretrial Services LEVEL 2 SUPERVISION.  Court reminders. No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with DW. Court advised Defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Aahlyric Conley appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Andrew Joel Golden appeared by video for Aahlyric Conley.  Prosecuting attorney Abby Rockendorf appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Skwierawski, Branch 41.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Court grants defense motion t o orally amend defendant's date of birth from 10/14/2000 to 10/04/2000. Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant pled not guilty. DEFENDANT DOES NOT QUALIFY FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION IF RELEASED FROM CUSTODY.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for December 2, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
